description.narrative: SBC empowered communities and facilitated positive social and behavioural change by influencing choices and decisions made by policymakers, service providers, communities, families, children and young people. SBC thus generated increased demand for basic services and created awareness of the need for quality services. Around 6 million people (52 per cent female) were regularly reached with development and emergency content, including on COVID-19 and vaccine uptake. ;Over 200,000 people were engaged, including persons with disabilities and refugee populations. Multiple channels including mass and social media, IoGT, and influencers such as faith leaders and youth volunteers were mobilized.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:04/01/2022
